"specific line is generally called **EOF** (End-Of-File) character. In a "
"default situation, every GMT command adds an EOF character in the end of the "
"output file, and when a PS file interpreter reads an EOF character, it would "
"stop reading. This is why we have run ``pscoast`` but it doesn't show on the "
"map. There is a universal option ``-K`` in GMT for this situation - it "
"prevents a GMT comment to add an EOF in the end of the output. In our case, "
