"the previous chapter, :ref:`some text describing basic information of the "
"map file <PS header>`. If there are two headers in one file, the PS "
"interpreter would read it incorrectly. Hence, there is also a universal "
"option ``-O``, which prevent a command from adding a header into the output "
"file. In our example, ``-O`` must be added at ``pscoast`` in order to not "
"put the second header in the middle of file, like this:"

